      <h5>Travel from further afield</h5>
      <p>If you're travelling from somewhere outside the UK directly to Italy, Rome will be best served by international flights, and is less than three hours from the venue by road or rail.</p>

      <hr />

      <h3><i class="icon fa-car"></i> Onward from the airport</h3>
      <p>The easiest option to reach Serre di Rapolano would be to hire a car at the airport you're flying into, or else to share with other guests who are doing so.  Due to its rural location, there is no station in the town itself.</p>
      <p>Alternatively, regular trains run from Rome (3h) and Pisa (2h30m) to Rapolano Terme, which is only a ten minute drive from Serre di Rapolano, and from which you could reach the venue by taxi or a lift from a friendly guest.  If you're choosing this option, flying to Pisa will be easiest as it's only a five minute taxi ride from the airport to the railway station.</p>
      <p>Train information and bookings can be found at <a href="http://www.trenitalia.com/tcom-en" target="_blank">Trenitalia</a>.

